message: Focus on using the 'stove' tool first to cook individual ingredients. Vegetables and proteins cooked with the stove reliably create 20-point 'cooked' items. Combining these cooked items significantly increases value: two cooked items often result in a 60-point item, and three cooked items often result in an 80-point item. Avoid the 'water' tool, as it typically reduces item value to 0. Aim for 80 points by combining a cooked protein, a cooked vegetable, and either a cooked grain or another cooked protein/vegetable.
